Evy Add-Ons Theme Storefront
üá¨üáß English
Description
Evy Add-Ons Theme Storefront is a consolidated WordPress plugin designed to enhance the Storefront theme for WooCommerce by combining essential functionalities. This plugin focuses on granular control over product visibility based on user roles and improved display of related products.

Key Features
Product Visibility by User Role:

Hides products within specified categories (e.g., "Short term accommodation") from general users.
Allows users with specific roles (e.g., tenant) to see only products within the otherwise restricted categories.
Administrators and Shop Managers (shop_manager) maintain full visibility of all products, without any restrictions.
This functionality applies to both the website frontend and the REST API (for WooCommerce mobile applications).
Related Products Enhancement:

Addresses limitations in the Storefront theme regarding cross-category related product displays.
Ensures that related products shown on single product pages are exclusively from the same category as the current product.
Installation
Download/Create Plugin Files:

Create a new folder named evy-add-ons-theme-storefront in your WordPress website's wp-content/plugins/ directory.
Inside the evy-add-ons-theme-storefront folder, create a file named evy-add-ons-theme-storefront.php.
Copy all the code provided in our conversation (the refined, clean version) and paste it into this evy-add-ons-theme-storefront.php file.
Deactivate Original Plugins:

Log in to your WordPress Admin Dashboard.
Navigate to Plugins.
Find and deactivate both original plugins:
OM SAB White House Add-Ons Hide Product slug
OM SAB Add-Ons Related Products on Theme Storefront
Activate New Plugin:

On the Plugins page, locate Evy Add-Ons Theme Storefront.
Click Activate.
Customizing User Roles and Product Categories
You can easily customize the user roles and product categories relevant to the product visibility feature by editing only the top section of the evy-add-ons-theme-storefront.php file:

PHP

// =================================================================================================
// üîß Section 1: User Role and Product Category Configuration (Edit this section only)
// =================================================================================================

/**
 * Function to get roles that have full access to all products (including restricted categories).
 * Add roles here if you want them to see all categories.
 * Example: ['administrator', 'shop_manager']
 */
function evy_get_full_access_roles() {
    return ['shop_manager'];
}

/**
 * Function to specify product category slugs that need restricted access.
 * Add the slugs of categories you want to restrict here.
 * Example: ['short_term_accommodation', 'special_offers']
 */
function evy_get_restricted_categories_slugs() {
    return ['short_term_accommodation'];
}

/**
 * Function to get roles allowed to access the restricted product categories.
 * Add roles here if you want them to see only the restricted categories.
 * Example: ['tenant', 'member']
 */
function evy_get_restricted_category_access_roles() {
    return ['tenant'];
}
By simply modifying the values within the return [...] arrays of these functions, you can define your desired roles and categories without altering any other part of the code.

